---
// Heart architecture diagram — pure inline SVG, no JS.
//
// Shows the journey of a single heartbeat: HW9 band (worn on the chest
// or upper / lower arm) detects an R-wave, broadcasts bpm + RR intervals
// over BLE GATT (char 0x2A37), the phone captures the frame, logs it
// locally, and an on-device compute pipeline derives HRV / sleep /
// rhythm / readiness / strain. Everything stays on the phone — no
// server, no cloud, no telemetry.
//
// Design constraints (mirrors components/ArchitectureDiagram.astro):
//   - No JS, no client-side rendering. SVG inlined at build time.
//   - Text in monospace to match the editorial / terminal-panel style.
//   - Site palette only — accent #00d4aa, surface #131316, bg #0b0b0d,
//     border #23232a, secondary #a3a3a3, hint #737373.
//   - Wraps in <figure> with <figcaption> so screen readers get a
//     plain-text equivalent of the diagram.
//   - viewBox-based, so it scales down to mobile without media queries.
---

<figure class="my-8">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 800 500"
    class="w-full h-auto max-w-3xl mx-auto block"
    role="img"
    aria-labelledby="heart-arch-title heart-arch-desc"
  >
    <title id="heart-arch-title">Heart architecture diagram</title>
    <desc id="heart-arch-desc">
      A heartbeat detected by the HW9 band — worn on the chest, upper
      arm, or forearm — is broadcast over BLE GATT as bpm and
      RR-interval values, captured by a background service on the
      phone, appended to an on-disk JSONL log, and fed through an
      on-device compute pipeline (HRV, sleep, rhythm, readiness,
      strain) that produces the live UI and Insights. No server,
      account, cloud sync, telemetry, or external model file is part of
      this picture.
    </desc>

    <!-- ── HW9 BAND (CHEST OR ARM) ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <rect x="40" y="40" width="220" height="340" rx="14"
            fill="#131316" stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="150" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">HW9 BAND · CHEST OR ARM</text>

      <!-- Heartbeat (ECG) -->
      <rect x="60" y="90" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="150" y="113" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#ffffff">Heartbeat (ECG)</text>

      <!-- arrow down -->
      <path d="M 150 130 L 150 144 M 146 140 L 150 144 L 154 140"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- bpm + RR ms -->
      <rect x="60" y="148" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="150" y="171" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">bpm + RR ms</text>

      <!-- arrow down -->
      <path d="M 150 188 L 150 202 M 146 198 L 150 202 L 154 198"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- BLE GATT 2A37 -->
      <rect x="60" y="206" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="150" y="229" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">BLE GATT · 0x2A37</text>

      <!-- Device boundary -->
      <text x="150" y="261" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">DEVICE BOUNDARY</text>
      <line x1="60" y1="270" x2="240" y2="270"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            stroke-opacity="0.55"/>

      <!-- BLE frame on the wire -->
      <rect x="60" y="284" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="150" y="307" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#737373">BLE notify frame</text>

      <!-- arrow exiting device -->
      <path d="M 150 332 L 150 374 M 146 370 L 150 374 L 154 370"
            stroke="#737373" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
    </g>

    <!-- ── CENTER · BLE CHANNEL ────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <text x="400" y="60" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">BLE 4.0+ · LINK-LAYER ENCRYPTED</text>

      <!-- Single horizontal pipe -->
      <line x1="260" y1="240" x2="540" y2="240"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <rect x="320" y="230" width="160" height="20" rx="10"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
      <text x="400" y="244" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            fill="#00d4aa">BLE notify · ~1 Hz</text>

      <!-- Range annotation -->
      <text x="400" y="290" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">DIRECT · NO RELAY · &lt; 10 m</text>

      <!-- Wire-bytes annotation -->
      <text x="400" y="335" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">ON THE WIRE</text>
      <text x="400" y="352" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#a3a3a3">bpm + RR ms only</text>
    </g>

    <!-- ── YOUR PHONE ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <rect x="540" y="40" width="220" height="340" rx="14"
            fill="#131316" stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="650" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">YOUR PHONE</text>

      <!-- arrow entering device from below -->
      <path d="M 650 374 L 650 332 M 646 336 L 650 332 L 654 336"
            stroke="#737373" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- Captured BLE frame -->
      <rect x="560" y="284" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="650" y="307" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#737373">BLE service · capture</text>

      <!-- Device boundary -->
      <line x1="560" y1="270" x2="740" y2="270"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            stroke-opacity="0.55"/>
      <text x="650" y="261" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">ON-DEVICE BOUNDARY</text>

      <!-- JSONL log -->
      <rect x="560" y="218" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="650" y="241" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">JSONL log · sandboxed</text>

      <!-- arrow up -->
      <path d="M 650 214 L 650 200 M 646 204 L 650 200 L 654 204"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- On-device compute (taller box, two lines) -->
      <rect x="560" y="142" width="180" height="58" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="650" y="164" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">HRV · Sleep · Rhythm</text>
      <text x="650" y="184" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">Readiness · Strain</text>

      <!-- arrow up -->
      <path d="M 650 138 L 650 124 M 646 128 L 650 124 L 654 128"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- Live UI · Insights -->
      <rect x="560" y="88" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="650" y="111" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#ffffff">Live UI · Insights</text>
    </g>

    <!-- ── BOTTOM BAND · NOT IN THE PICTURE ────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <line x1="40" y1="410" x2="760" y2="410"
            stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="400" y="438" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">NOT IN THE PICTURE</text>
      <text x="400" y="468" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#a3a3a3">No server · No account · No cloud sync · No telemetry · No model file</text>
    </g>
  </svg>

  <figcaption class="text-hint text-xs font-mono text-center mt-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
    A heartbeat detected by the HW9 band — worn on the chest, upper arm, or forearm — travels as bpm + RR-interval values over a short-range BLE link directly to your phone, where it is logged locally and fed through an on-device compute pipeline. No server, cloud sync, telemetry, or external model file is involved.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
